observations.recommendation:
We recommended that Management:
facilitate the submission of the Summary of Supplies and Materials Issued (SSMI) together with the Distribution List of the goods consumed/distributed in CY 2020 to the Accounting Office in order to record the supplies and materials as expenses and drop the corresponding inventory accounts from the books;
require the GSO/Inventory Committee to conduct physical count of inventory items on a semestral basis and prepare and submit the corresponding report to the Audit Team;
require the GSO to prepare and submit the Summary of Supplies and Materials Issued (SSMI) together with the supporting Requisition and Issue Slip (RIS) to the Accounting Office monthly for proper recording of consumed supplies and materials as expenses; and
require the GSO to maintain stock cards (SCs) for each type of inventory and periodically reconcile the same with the supplies ledger card being maintained in the Accounting Office.

We recommend that Management direct the:

Municipal Treasurer to adopt the imprest system in the payment of financial assistance;

Petty Cash Custodian and Municipal Treasurer to strictly adhere to the minimum documentary requirements prescribed under COA Circular No. 2012-01 in granting cash advance requests for PCF;

grant of cash advance to the Petty Cash Custodian in accordance with her accountability in the fidelity bond; and

Municipal Accountant to use the proper journal entries to Petty Cash Fund in accordance with the imprest system of accounting for petty cash.

We recommended that Management: 

exert effort to facilitate the approval of the LGU’s SWM Plan for proper, clearer, timely and systematic implementation of SWM; 
implement and closely monitor significant SWM PPAs as planned and budgeted to maximize the benefits that could be derived therefrom; 


willfully enforce existing ordinances and their penalties and/or incentives and/or add SWM ordinances, if necessary, to effectively implement SWM; 


adopt additional specific revenue-generating measures to promote the viability of the LGU’s Solid Waste Management Plan; and


hasten the completion of the LGU’s Materials Recovery Facility (MRF) and Residual Containment Area (RCA) as well as complete closure of the existing dumpsite according to the set timeline.

We recommended that Management direct the:
Municipal Treasurer to adopt the imprest system in the payment of financial assistance;
Petty Cash Custodian and Municipal Treasurer to strictly adhere to the minimum documentary requirements prescribed under COA Circular No. 2012-01 in granting cash advance requests for PCF;
grant of cash advance to the Petty Cash Custodian in accordance with her accountability in the fidelity bond; and
Municipal Accountant to use the proper journal entries to Petty Cash Fund in accordance with the imprest system of accounting for petty cash and COA Circular No. 2015-009.

observations.managementAction:
Implementation of the following planned PPAs under the 70 per cent MF:

Flood, Earthquake, Fire and Tsunami Evacuation Drill;

Procurement of School-Based Earthquake Survival Kit;

Procurement of Personal Protective Equipment (PPEs) for MDRRMC Volunteers;

Procurement of 4X4 pick-up truck rescue vehicle; and

Activation of Incident Command System (ICS)

The following activities in relation to the closure of the dumpsite and construction of a proper Materials Recovery Facility were completed:

Levelling up of the entire garbage area and covering it with soil;

Putting up of gas vent in the covered garbage;

Construction of Pathwalk to the exit area of water from site; and

Completion of wall beside the dumping area

observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Management:

require the concerned officers and employees to immediately settle/liquidate their outstanding cash advances thru the submission of duly accomplished liquidation reports otherwise, enforce the withholding of salary;

stop the grant of additional cash advances for travel to all personnel with unliquidated cash advances until such time previous cash advances are fully settled;

exert necessary effort to locate supporting documents and establish the validity of the receivables under labeled with “carried forward balances” or request for write-off of the accounts, if warranted; and

monitor and establish controls to ensure the timely liquidation of cash advances through updated monthly aging of the same to prevent accumulation of unliquidated cash advances.

Management is advised to:

require the concerned officers and employees to immediately settle/liquidate their outstanding cash advances thru the submission of duly accomplished liquidation reports otherwise, enforce the withholding of salary, in accordance with Section 5.1.3 of COA Circular No. 97-002;

stop the grant of additional cash advances for travel to all personnel with unliquidated cash advances until such time previous cash advances are fully settled;

exert necessary effort to locate supporting documents and establish the validity of the receivables under labeled with “carried forward balances” or request for write-off of the accounts, if warranted; and

monitor and establish controls to ensure the timely liquidation of cash advances through updated monthly aging of the same to prevent accumulation of unliquidated cash advances.

We recommended and Management agreed to:
adhere strictly with Section 3 of COA Circular No. 2009-001 and Section 4(6) of PD 1445 at all times and submit/attach complete contract documents and required supporting documents to government disbursements;
submit immediately the subject/needed lacking supporting documents to facilitate technical review and evaluation of the completed projects;
refrain from approving government claims with incomplete supporting documents.

We recommended that Management:
exert effort to facilitate the approval of the LGU’s SWM Plan for proper, clearer, timely and systematic implementation of SWM;
implement and closely monitor significant SWM PPAs as planned and budgeted to maximize the benefits that could be derived therefrom;
willfully enforce existing ordinances and their penalties and/or incentives and/or add SWM ordinances, if necessary, to effectively implement SWM;
adopt additional specific revenue-generating measures to promote the viability of the LGU’s Solid Waste Management Plan; and
